Had to stop and try it out considering the history.  Who doesn't luv hotdogs? These were quite special and we didn't have to wait in an enormous line either! Being from the east coast I had to the Brooklyn dog and wasn't disappointed. Make it a stop on your NY travels.

Been coming to this place since I was a kid. When my grandmother would come Downtown to get whatever, I'd always ask, "Can we go get hot dogs today, Ma?" When It was Abraham & Strauss, before it was Macy's. When the names Woolworths, May's, and McCrory's graces what is now known as Fulton Mall. It's changed several names, but it's still Downtown Brooklyn's favorite hot dog spot this side of Nathan's. I get what I always get. Two with mustard and a pineapple juice. My lady had the sausage with mustard, ketchup, onions, and relish. No disrespect to Nathan's, or Gray's Papaya, but this all Downtown Brooklyn! The go to spot for a quick bite! For me, it's great memories and I'll always love this place!

Cons: the only bad thing to say is you have to eat standing up there is nowhere for you to sit there's nowhere for you to rest your food to eat you have to eat your food kind of outside not really a good option if you're looking to dine in but a really good option if you need food on the go.  Pro:Considering the price and considering the quality of the hot dog they have all beef hot dogs I didn't really see an option for vegans or for chicken or turkey 100% beef hot dogs made fresh to order for about $2.50 per hot dog really good cheap eats check it out. I used to frequent this spot when I was a teenager and was running the streets shopping with friends downtown Brooklyn. I stopped by today because my mom wanted a hot dog. We passed a few hot dog stands and Im like uhmm where are you going? She says she has a spot where she goes for her hot dogs and sausages and lo and behold it was here. The place looked the same with some extra menu items. I was shocked when the worker behind the counter knew my mom, I was like dang you come here that often. She said she stops by whenever she's in the area.  They have like four or five bar seats all the way in the back and dont get too comfy back there because if more than two people sit there you will be cramped, LOL. Now to the food, I ordered a sausage with a small pineapple juice and devoured both. I wasnt even that hungry but since my mom was treating I couldnt resist and boy was I surprised. That sausage was goood and hit the spot. All I had on it was mustard and ketchup and it was umm umm delicious. It had the nice amount of spiciness and wasnt overcooked.  I shouldve ordered one to go.  I wont forget this corner spot in the future and will check it out when I want some cheap good eats.
